						<summary>

						<p>This undated inscription records that the Noḻamba-Pallava king <hi rend="bold">Noḻambādhirāja</hi> granted <hi rend="bold">Piriya-Meḻapi</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Bāḷasōma-Bhaṭāra,</hi> in the month of Pushya, Jupiter being in Makara. Noḻambādhirāja of Nos. 32-37 has probably to be identified with <hi rend="bold">Iṟiva-Noḻamba Noḷipayya</hi> as the records are written in characters of the 10th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
